United States Agency for International Development has drastically reduced the fish-for-sex trade along the shores of Lake Victoria in Busia county.It has supported poor women to start their own businesses, so they don&rsquo;t have to trade sex for fish from fishermen, so that they can sell fish.It has also created awareness about HIV-Aids and unprotected sex.Busia health officials praised USAid when they met the agency&rsquo;s head of Health for the Africa Bureau Lisa Baldwin. Baldwin (pictured) visited Tororo, Busia and Malaba districts of Uganda at Sio Port to assess USAid&rsquo;s funding of the crossborder Health Integrated Partnership Project. It is conducted through Family Health International 360. Kenyan and Ugandan delegations attended the meeting.